   "source": [
    "# Quickstart\n",
    "\n",
    "In this quickstart, we show how to model a multivariate dataset\n",
    "and then generate a synthetic data that resembles it."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x288 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {

     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "from copulas.datasets import sample_trivariate_xyz\n",
    "from copulas.multivariate import GaussianMultivariate\n",
    "from copulas.visualization import compare_3d\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load a dataset with 3 columns that are not independent\n",
    "real_data = sample_trivariate_xyz()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fit a gaussian copula to the data\n",
    "copula = GaussianMultivariate()\n",
    "copula.fit(real_data)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Sample synthetic data\n",
    "synthetic_data = copula.sample(len(real_data))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot the real and the synthetic data to compare\n",
    "compare_3d(real_data, synthetic_data)"
   ]
  }
